ed since ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1962-10-11/s603"},"text":"section 603 of the Act of Oct. 11, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/793"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–793","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/847"},"text":"76 Stat. 847","children":[],"tail":", eliminated the necessity of referring to rates as scheduled or longevity."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(B), the words “except a hearing examiner appointed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3105"},"text":"section 3105 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are added on authority of the third sentence of former section 1010 and the fifth sentence of former section 1011, which are carried into sections 5362 and 559, respectively, and of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-10-28/ch782/s1106/a"},"text":"section 1106(a) of the Act of Oct. 28, 1949, ch. 782","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/972"},"text":"63 Stat. 972","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Title VII (sections 701–705) of the ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-10-28/ch782"},"text":"Act of Oct. 28, 1949, ch. 782","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/967-969"},"text":"63 Stat. 967–969","children":[],"tail":", as amended by the following Acts is omitted from the derivation and repealed (see Table II) as superseded by the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/793/s603"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–793, § 603","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/847"},"text":"76 Stat. 847","children":[],"tail":", which is carried into this section and section 5336:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/u